last day in NYC. I love this city. The neighborhoods are pretty, there are many parks where you could take a stroll then just sit on a bench and read a book, lovely museums like The Met and MoMA (and many others i haven't explored yet) pretty sunsets from Brooklyn Bridge, sunlight coming through the buildings during the afternoon, and most of the people here are friendly - you could just say hi and stop for a while for a friendly chat. Sure, not all parts of the city are pretty, but i really love it here. I'm going to miss NYC so much, hopefully i will get back here soon❤️
